children.subject: ^Why is cs170 not expanding? past year they all expand to a capacity of 800-900

history.content:
We always recommend having a backup plan when you are on any wait list. Each professor who teaches a class gets to manage their enrollment capacity and wait list as they think is best. Just because a class has expanded exponentially in the past, doesn't mean it will do so during the current semester.

It may seem that we have the ability to expand infinitely since classes are being taught remotely but that isn't true. We still need enough TAs to facilitate discussion sections online and that means we may be constrained by the hiring budget. 

I know it's challenging to keep up with all the work if you aren't going to get into a class and you want answers now. In this case, I still haven't heard final enrollment information for CS 170 - it's a fluid situation as faculty do what they can to expand AND there are no guarantees it will be able to expand further.

Hi! 

I am currently #25 on the waitlist for CS170. I noticed that the waitlist has approximately ~ 70 students in it right now. I know historically most students get off the waitlist, but the add/drop deadline is in about a week (9/16). I was wondering if there was a chance the class would expand to incorporate all the students on the waitlist or will I not be able to get into the class? For context, I am not a declared CS major. Should I try to find another class or is there a high chance that I will be able to enroll?

Thank you!
